author: @choerrymotion
text:
why ‘best of me’ is one of bts’ best songs to date: 
a lecture by @choerrymotion lol

this song is incredibly catchy. i mean, i hadn’t heard of bts or ‘best of me’ yet i somehow knew the chorus. it’s not like other tracks in kpop, it doesn’t condone to the typical kpop sound that is usually seen throughout the genre. that being said, it doesn’t sound westernised either. it’s one of a kind, a song that follows patterns that cannot be repeated. 

not only is the melody great, but the tone in the song is amazing. usually, bts songs are quite high and they do not fit taehyung’s lower vocals as well as they fit jungkook’s higher vocals. however, with this song, taehyung’s vocals fit extremely well as well as jungkook and jimin’s high vocals fitting too. this song has parts where all members can showcase their talents. jin is known to get very few lines yet in this song, it shows that he sings one of the most iconic ones. the rap line have fast paced raps that add to the excitement of the song, namjoon yoongi and hoseok’s verses prove to be a great asset to this b-side. 

lastly, i wanted to talk about the choreography. the choreography is very appealing to watch and fits the song very well. whenever i listen to ‘best of me’, i can visually imagine bts performing it in my head. during the “haru” section that jin sings, bts can be seen walking in a straight line beside each other. this, not only, shows unity but it also fits the dynamic of the music with the dynamic of the movement. 

okay so, there’s more i could say but you all probably don’t have time, so in conclusion, 
‘best of me’ is a masterpiece that is honestly worth your time and recognition. this could be title track material! 

thank you for reading my ted talk on why ‘best of me’ deserves more. 
@choerrymotion

author: @irene.356
text:
Todos hablando de Jimin.. Yo hablare de los demás.

La voz de Jin estuvo HERMOSA, también la voz profunda de TaeTae, me encanta la visual line ❤
Jungkook el vocalista principal siempre luciendose y opacando con lo visual que es y la HERMOSISIMA voz de ángel que tiene 😘
La parte de RM me encanto marik, el es un Lindo Bebe con mucho talento, igual Yoongi el siempre llamando la atención en cada uno de sus performance, sin duda puedo decir que el me sorprendio mucho.
Hobi, mi sunshine, su baile fue el MEJOR, tiene mucho potencial en el baile, me encanta la forma en que su cuerpito se mueve, ese es mi Bailarin Principal, mi sol, lo amo mucho 😊

Esta bien tener bias, nadie se lo prohibe, creo que todas tienen bias, hasta yo, pero hay MUCHAS ARMYS que tienen preferencias y lo ÚNICO que ven es el Visual y no el talento ni el potencial que los demás ponen. No entiendan mal, Jimin también es muy talentoso y lindo pero bajenle un poco, que TODOS lo son por igual, nadie es mejor que nadie. Y no lo nieguen vi comentarios menospreciando.

LOS AMO MUCHO A LOS SIETE, SON LOS LINDOS BEBES DE ARMY 💜

author: @Raziel8385
text:
Good lord, RM is killing me! Those burning sexy eyes looking right into the camera and into my soul. His dancing is so good now, he's really getting those body rolls and slight movements down now. I'm sure he's been working so hard, and it really shows. He's not so stiff and robotic anymore but when doing the more difficult moves, his face still gets very focused. You can tell he is really thinking about the moves as he does them. I'm so proud of him! And he's just so damn gorgeous lol. Even if his dancing never improved and he wasn't that handsome, he would still be my bias. I absolutely love his voice, the way he conveys emotion and his level of passion. He's a lyrical genius and a master at arranging, mixing, and producing. They say he writes and expresses himself are captivating. Suga is also right up there and it's a pretty close tie, but RM is still my top choice. Even though I love every single member and the beauty and fun that they bring to the group. 
I love you BTS! Thank you for being you and sharing your passion, message and talent with the world. 
Love yourself! Love Myself! 
Stay strong, happy, healthy and safe!

author: @aaliyahdell3488
text: So I had a crazy idea and I know that no one will probably do it, but I at least want to try. BTS has done a lot and is still doing wonders for not just ARMY but people that somewhat know them. A lot of ARMY are showing their gratitude and I want to do so also but not in a money type way. I wanted to write letters but it takes time and money to send letters that may never reach them and I'll probably never meet them, but if anyone wants to join in and help me they can. I wanted to do a hashtag, but I don't have twitter and I don't know how to use it either, so I can't do it there. This is the only way for me to communicate. The hashtag was #BtsInspiresMeTo. It's been 5 years since these boys have debuted (not sure what month) and I want to spread love, so please if you can please spread this hashtag if you'd like. It'd mean a lot to me and even if you don't, thank you for those that read this comment. I guess I'll be the first. #BTSInspiresMeTo lose weight, push myself to the best of my abilities, and to be myself. I'm still trying to find out who I am in this world, and these 7 brothers of ours are really helping. Thank you BTS and a hue thank you to ARMY.

author: @chloehadjard
text:
I saw some people bringing up the fact that they (obviously) used autotune for this performance. Well... of course they did. The song requires powerful and steady vocals and this is near impossible with this choreo, which seems super tiring, without using some autotune. If you don't like the sound of it you can still watch their performance from tbe 4th muster but they don't dance for the whole song.
I don't mean to rant, but people need to understand that BTS are 7 human beings and there are some things that they can't do flawlessly so they need a little help and this time it came in the shape of autotune. Just trying to make a bit of peace.

EDIT: I must admit that the effect was pretty strong here, but the performance was still great and the dancing was on point

author: @mohamemedessalhi482
text:
In the comments, everyone is saying 'suga is the best', 'jungkook is my favourite', 'jimin i love you! You're the best', 'JIN OH MY GOD I LOVE YOU !!!! ' 'OMO RM !!! ' 'V i love you so so so so much!!' 'J-hope you killed me cuz ur the best.' GUYS stop comparing! I mean, it's not that you can't have a bias or smt like that, nor that they aren't cool. It could be nice for the member you're complementing(?) but it could not be nice for the others. We Stan a GROUP not a MEMBER. We Stan BTS not Joonie, Jinnie, lil meow meow, Hobi, Chim Chim, V (sorry I can't  remember any unsername since he doesn't like 'Alien') or kookie only. I hope you get what I mean and don't misunderstand. If you want to complement(?) smn then just say 'Bts i love you! You guys are very good! (we shouldn't compare in between the groups too, sorry if it's too much😆) ----- you're my bias! But you all are bias wrecking me! (if you say it's not true then you're lying)' or smt like that, then no one is going to be upset (i think). Btw sorry if it was too long for you. 
PS: I know that probably bts aren't reading our comments, but if they did at least once then no one is going to be upset.

i love bts and they are all so talented. When i started this video i was like omg they're singing live, but then i realized they could be lip syncing. Like i'm aware that this isn't the original voice track and their voices sound different and makes you think that they're singing live, but it could be recorded before this stage. The point where i thought about this was 0:45 on Seokjin's part where he kinda stops moving his lips even though it sounds like he's still singing. 

Don't get me wrong this is not hate, I love BTS. Every artist and group lipsync, yes it's true. If BTS was singing live, damn. If they weren't, still damn. It's still their voice and im very proud of them 💕

author: @evajaneschubert
text:
there is one problem with this fandom. aside from fangirling / fanboying when they post and getting excited when you hear their music, it’s also really depressing. like knowing your probably never going to meet them, for some people- never attend a concert etc. then im here crying after watching this bc I know im never going to meet them. and it honestly is heartbreaking. 

i love bts with all my heart and it’s amazing to be part of this fandom. they fill us all with joy and sadness- bring us hope to starting new things.  

it’s addictive really, like im happy when watching them, listening to them, then when im not i go really quiet. i don’t talk to anyone. as soon as I get home from anywhere ive got my earphones in and listening to them. 

don’t get me wrong, i love being a part of this fandom, and im glad that im in it, it’s just realisation of it all that just gets me.

author: @FizaGG
text:
Whenever I saw fans crying at concerts , I used to think that it was so stupid. 
But now I know that it's not something you can control if u Stan them so hard. I have been a fan of 1D n other artists but ever since I got to know these 7 dorks, nothing and no one else matters now. I feel all kinds of emotions when I see/hear them. 
I don't know why I cry when I watch their videos(never happened before), no matter what the content is. 
Bangtan is special to me. And I will never allow anyone to take that feeling away from me. They heal me in a way nothing/no one has ever done before... 
If I ever get the chance to see them, all I would ask of them is to never change,never part ways , and always be happy. 
Iam so proud of them and I will always pray for their success... 
Oh I Love You , my dorks.... 😭😭😭

author: @SpiritedDancer17
text:
You know you’re early when there’s only 12 dislikes. ✊🏻
But personally I feel like none of their videos should ever have thumbs down. 

Gosh I love them so much. You know the feeling when you love something/someone so much that it actually physically hurts?? My chest seriously hurts because I love them so much. I know part of it is also because I’m one in millions and millions of people who love them so I’m lost in the crowd. So how could they ever know or hear that I love them and how much they’ve made me smile and how much respect and gratitude I have for every single one of them? It makes me sad when someone has helped me get through some of the toughest things in life and I’m not able to repay them and thank them.
